"Juin S., Brisson N., Clastre P., Grand P.","Impact of global warming on the growing cycles of three forage systems in upland areas of southeastern France",2004,"Agronomie","24","6-7",,"327","337",,,10.1051/agro:2004028,"http://www.scopus.com/inward/record.url?eid=2-s2.0-9244224174&partnerID=40&md5=d78244bf6f62924933227cc32a594fc1","Dept. Environnement et Agronomie, U. Climat Sol et Environnement, INRA, Site Agroparc, 84914 Avignon, Cedex 9, France; Chambre d'Agric. Hautes Alpes S.J., Unité CSE, Ribiers, 05000 Gap, France","Juin, S., Dept. Environnement et Agronomie, U. Climat Sol et Environnement, INRA, Site Agroparc, 84914 Avignon, Cedex 9, France; Brisson, N., Dept. Environnement et Agronomie, U. Climat Sol et Environnement, INRA, Site Agroparc, 84914 Avignon, Cedex 9, France; Clastre, P., Dept. Environnement et Agronomie, U. Climat Sol et Environnement, INRA, Site Agroparc, 84914 Avignon, Cedex 9, France; Grand, P., Chambre d'Agric. Hautes Alpes S.J., Unité CSE, Ribiers, 05000 Gap, France","The simulations supplied by a combination of a global climate model and a weather generator allowed the creation of two climate scenarios including an increase and/or monthly variations in temperature for the 2070-2100 horizon, which were compared with two currently available series (1961-1990 and 1990-2000). Three forage systems applied in upland areas of southern France were simulated using the STICS model (silage maize, perennial alfalfa and grasses) and the outputs were introduced into a digital elevation model. We noted changes in precocity which allowed the sowing of silage maize varieties with longer crop cycles at lower altitudes and an enlargement of the crop zone above 700-800 m. When introducing monthly temperature variations, we observed major frost damage which decreased maize yields. As for gramineous and alfalfa grasslands, we obtained a lengthening in the growing period with earlier first cut dates and sometimes the possibility of a supplementary cut.","Alfalfa, gramineous; Climatic change; Crop model; Silage maize; Upland area","agricultural modeling; cropping practice; forage; global warming; sowing date; Eastern Hemisphere; Eurasia; Europe; France; Western Europe; World; Medicago sativa; Poaceae; Zea mays",,,,,,"Antonioletti, R., (1986) Contribution à l'Étude du Mont Ventoux, , Note de l'INRA, Avignon; Antonioletti, R., Seguin, B., Quelques éléments sur le climat du mont Ventoux (1988) Bulletin Clim. et Agroclim. de Vaucluse, pp. 26-34. , Avignon; Baragnon, G., (2003) Analyse Bayésienne Rétrospective d'Une Rupture Dans des Séries Phénologiques, , INRA, Montpellier; Barthelet, P., Bony, S., Braconnot, P., Braun, A., Cariolle, D., Cohen-Solal, E., Dufresne, J.-L., Valcke, S., Simulations couplées globales des changements climatiques associés à une augmentation de la teneur atmosphérique en CO2 (1998) C.R. Acad. Sci. Paris, Sér. II A, 326, pp. 677-684; Bolstad, P.V., Swift, L., Collins, F., Régnière, J., Measured and predicted air temperatures at basin regional scales in the southern Appalachian mountains (1998) Agric. For. Meteorol., 91, pp. 161-176; Bootsma, A., Forage crop maturity zonation in the Atlantic region using growing degree-days (1984) Can. J. Plant Sci., 64, pp. 329-338; Brisson, N., Mary, B., Ripoche, D., Jeuffroy, M.H., Ruget, F., Nicoullaud, B., Gate, P., Delecolle, R., STICS: A generic model for simulating of crops and their water and nitrogen balances. I. Theory and parameterization applied to wheat and corn (1998) Agronomie, 18, pp. 311-346; Brisson, N., Domergue, M., (2003) Phenological Modeling and Climate Change Impacts in Orchards: Examples of Apple, Peach and Apricot Trees in the Rhone Valley (France). Towards An Operational System for Monitoring, Modeling, and Forecasting of Phenological Changes and Their Socio-economic Impacts, , Environmental Systems Analysis Group, Wageningen; Brisson, N., Gary, C., Juste, E., Roche, R., Mary, B., Ripoche, D., Zimmer, D., Sinoquet, H., An overview of the crop model STICS (2003) Eur. J. Agron., 18, pp. 309-332; Choisnel, E., Aspects topographiques : Une méthodologie d'étude en région de moyenne montagne (1986) Agrométéorologie des Régions de Moyenne Montagne, , Les colloques de l'INRA, Paris; Cooper, G., Mac Gechan, M.B., Implications of an altered climate for forage conservation (1996) Agric. For. Meteorol., 79, pp. 253-269; Davies, A., Shao, J., Brignall, P., Bardgette, R.D., Parry, M.L., Pollock, C.J., Specification of climatic sensitivity of forage maize to climate change (1996) Grass Forage Sci., 51, pp. 306-317; Delecolle, R., Jayet, P.A., Soussana, J.F., Agriculture française et effet de serre : Quelques éléments de réflexion (2000) Impacts Potentiels du Changement Climatique en France Au XXIe Siècle, pp. 74-80. , M.I.E.S; Douguedroit, A., (1986) Les Topoclimats Thermiques de Moyenne Montagne. Agromété orologie des Régions de Moyenne Montagne, pp. 198-213. , Les colloques de l'INRA, Toulouse; Fagerberg, B., Phenological development in timothy, red clover and Lucerne (1988) Acta Agric. Scand., 38, pp. 159-170; Fleury, P., (1985) La Variabilité Microclimatique en Montagne, Son Expression Par la Phénologie du Dactyle des Prairies Permanentes, , département de recherches sur les systèmes agraires et le développement; Gillet, M., Les graminées fourragères, description, fonctionnement, applications à la culture de l'herbe (1979) Collection « Nature et Agriculture », , Gauthier-Villars, Paris; Grand, P., (1991) Référentiel Fourrages, Provence Alpes Cote d'Azur, Pratiques Culturales et Utilisations des Fourrages Observées Dans Les Petites Régions Naturelles, Références Techniques Pour l'Élaboration de Systèmes Fourragers, , Maison régionale de l'élevage; Guy, P., Blondon, F., Durand, J., Action de la température et de la durée d'éclairement sur la croissance et la floraison de deux types éloignés de luzerne cultivée (1971) Ann. Amélior. Plantes, 21, pp. 409-422; Guyot, G., (1997) Climatologie de l'Environnement : De la Plante Aux Écosystè mes, , Masson, Paris; (2001) Climate Change 2001 : The Scientific Basis; Juin, S., (2001) Impact du Réchauffement Climatique Sur la Répartition Géographique et Les Calendriers de Production de Trois Systèmes Fourragers, , Diplôme Agronomie Approfondie, Montpellier; Le Maho, Y., Georges, J.-Y., Réponses des écosystèmes marins et insulaires aux changements climatiques (2003) Geoscience, 335, pp. 551-560; Le Treut, H., Les scénarios globaux de changement climatique et leurs incertitudes (2003) Geoscience, 335, pp. 525-533; Leland Russell, F., Louda, S.M., (2003) Phenological Synchrony in the Prediction of Insect; Herbivore Impacts on Native Plant Populations. Towards An Operational System for Monitoring, Modeling, and Forecasting of Phenological Changes and Their Socio-economic Impacts, , Environmental Systems Analysis Group, Wageningen; Lobell, D.B., Asner, G.P., Climate and management Contributions to recent Trends in US Agricultural Yields (2003) Science, 299, pp. 10-32; Lookingbill, T.R., Urban, D.L., Spatial estimation of air temperature differences for landscape-scale studies in mountain environments (2003) Agric. For. Meteorol., 114, pp. 141-151; Mavromatis, T., Hansen, J.W., Interannual variability characteristics and simulated crop responses of four stochastic weather generators (2001) Agric. For. Meteorol., 109, pp. 283-296; Niqueux, M., Arnaud, R., Étude du rythme de végétation des graminées fourragères : Cas de la moyenne montagne (1985) Fourrages, 103, pp. 31-54; Olesen, J.E., Bindi, M., Consequences of climate change for European agricultural productivity, land use and policy (2002) Eur. J. Agron., 16, pp. 239-262; Peiris, D.R., Crawford, J.W., Grashoff, C., Jefferies, R.A., Porter, J.R., Marshall, B., A simulation study of crop growth and development under climate change (1996) Agric. For. Meteorol., 79, pp. 271-287; Penuelas, J., Filella, I., Stefanescu, C., Llones, L., Ogaya, R., (2003) Plant and Animal Phenological Change Linked to R